<BaseLayout title="Contact & Corrections" description="Contact Dama Korea to report a correction, suggest a practical guide or ask about the site."><section class="page-hero"><div class="shell"><span class="eyebrow">Contact</span><h1>Help us keep the details useful.</h1><p>Report changed information, suggest a guide or ask a question about how the site works.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="article-shell article-body"><div class="quick-answer"><strong>Email the editorial desk</strong><a href="mailto:support@damaheritage.com">support@damaheritage.com</a></div><h2>For a correction</h2><ul class="checklist"><li>Include the URL of the page.</li><li>Quote the sentence or section that may be wrong.</li><li>Explain what changed and when you observed it.</li><li>Include an official source or screenshot when available.</li></ul><h2>For a guide suggestion</h2><p>Tell us the practical problem, who encounters it and what existing guides fail to explain. We prioritize topics that affect international visitors or residents and can be verified responsibly.</p><h2>Response and privacy</h2><p>Email is handled only for the purpose of responding, investigating a correction or managing the site. Do not send passport copies, residence numbers, banking records or other sensitive personal documents.</p></div></section></BaseLayout>
